{"parse":{"title":"Ari Elon","pageid":37813899,"revid":816585334,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ari_Elon.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Ari_Elon.jpg/220px-Ari_Elon.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Ari_Elon.jpg/330px-Ari_Elon.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Ari_Elon.jpg/440px-Ari_Elon.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1600\" data-file-height=\"1200\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ari_Elon.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ari Elon</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Ari Elon</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Hebrew\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hebrew\">Hebrew</a>: \u05d0\u05e8\u05d9 \u05d0\u05dc\u05d5\u05df) (born 1950) is an Israeli writer, a Talmud scholar and educator.\n</p><p>Elon was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Jerusalem\" title=\"Jerusalem\">Jerusalem</a> in 1950. He is the son of former <a href=\"/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_Israel\" title=\"Supreme Court of Israel\">Israel Supreme Court</a> Justice <a href=\"/wiki/Menachem_Elon\" title=\"Menachem Elon\">Menachem Elon</a>. Elon's brothers include the late Israeli politician, MK <a href=\"/wiki/Binyamin_Elon\" title=\"Binyamin Elon\">Benny Elon</a>, disgraced Rabbi <a href=\"/wiki/Mordechai_Elon\" title=\"Mordechai Elon\">Mordechai Elon</a> and Be'er Sheva District Court Judge <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Joseph_(%22Sefi%22)_Elon&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Joseph (&quot;Sefi&quot;) Elon (page does not exist)\">Joseph (\"Sefi\") Elon</a> . \n</p><p>Despite his family's religious background, he became secular at a young age.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He taught Talmud and Midrash at <a href=\"/wiki/The_Hebrew_University_of_Jerusalem\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Hebrew University of Jerusalem\">The Hebrew University of Jerusalem</a>. Elon taught at various institutions throughout Israel, including <a href=\"/wiki/BINA_Center_for_Jewish_Identity_and_Hebrew_Culture\" title=\"BINA Center for Jewish Identity and Hebrew Culture\">BINA Center for Jewish Identity and Hebrew Culture</a>, and served as the director of the Rabbinic Texts Program at the <a href=\"/wiki/Reconstructionist_Rabbinical_College\" title=\"Reconstructionist Rabbinical College\">Reconstructionist Rabbinical College</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Philadelphia\" title=\"Philadelphia\">Philadelphia</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Published_works\">Published works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ari_Elon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Published works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>From Jerusalem to the Edge of Heaven</i>, Jewish Publication Society, 1996</li>\n<li><i>Trees, Earth, and Torah: A Tu B'Shvat Anthology</i>,  (Editor) The Jewish Publication Society, 2000</li>\n<li><i>Ba el ha-\u1e33odesh&#160;: 36 agadot nistarot</i>, Yedi\u02bbot a\u1e25aronot, 2005</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ari_Elon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.haaretz.com/weekend/magazine/because-judaism-isn-t-a-dirty-word-1.209168\">Because Judaism isn't a dirty word</a>, haaretz,1,4, 2007</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1266\nCached time: 20180908174202\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.032 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.047 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 92/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 308/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 72/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 476/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.003/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 525 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   22.860      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   22.860      1 -total\n  7.96%    1.819      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:37813899-0!canonical and timestamp 20180908174202 and revision id 816585334\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"he","url":"https://he.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D7%90%D7%A8%D7%99_%D7%90%D7%9C%D7%95%D7%9F","langname":"Hebrew","autonym":"\u05e2\u05d1\u05e8\u05d9\u05ea","*":"\u05d0\u05e8\u05d9 \u05d0\u05dc\u05d5\u05df"}],"categories":[{"sortkey":"Elon, Ari","*":"1950_births"},{"sortkey":"Elon, Ari","*":"Israeli_biblical_scholars"},{"sortkey":"Elon, Ari","*":"Jewish_biblical_scholars"},{"sortkey":"Elon, Ari","*":"Judaic_studies"},{"sortkey":"Elon, Ari","*":"Living_people"},{"sortkey":"Elon, Ari","*":"Elon_family"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"BINA Center for Jewish Identity and Hebrew Culture"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Binyamin Elon"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Hebrew"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Jerusalem"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Menachem Elon"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Mordechai Elon"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Philadelphia"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Reconstructionist Rabbinical College"}